{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":709,"text":"Type is something we consume"},{"time":2235,"text":"in enormous quantities."},{"time":4157,"text":"In much of the world,"},{"time":5239,"text":"it's completely inescapable."},{"time":7107,"text":"But few consumers are concerned to know"},{"time":10130,"text":"where a particular typeface came from"},{"time":12462,"text":"or when or who designed it,"},{"time":15226,"text":"if, indeed, there was any human agency involved"},{"time":18579,"text":"in its creation, if it didn't just sort of materialize"},{"time":21376,"text":"out of the software ether."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25088,"text":"But I do have to be concerned with those things."},{"time":28613,"text":"It's my job."},{"time":30130,"text":"I'm one of the tiny handful of people"},{"time":32340,"text":"who gets badly bent out of shape"},{"time":34454,"text":"by the bad spacing of the T and the E"},{"time":37048,"text":"that you see there."},{"time":38948,"text":"I've got to take that slide off."},{"time":40390,"text":"I can't stand it. Nor can Chris."},{"time":42461,"text":"There. Good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":44122,"text":"So my talk is about the connection"},{"time":45890,"text":"between technology and design of type."},{"time":49290,"text":"The technology has changed"},{"time":51953,"text":"a number of times since I started work:"},{"time":54825,"text":"photo, digital, desktop, screen, web."},{"time":59486,"text":"I've had to survive those changes and try"},{"time":61224,"text":"to understand their implications for what I do"},{"time":63928,"text":"for design."},{"time":65319,"text":"This slide is about the effect of tools on form."},{"time":70489,"text":"The two letters, the two K's,"},{"time":73390,"text":"the one on your left, my right, is modern,"},{"time":76715,"text":"made on a computer."},{"time":78126,"text":"All straight lines are dead straight."},{"time":80168,"text":"The curves have that kind of\nmathematical smoothness"},{"time":82978,"text":"that the Bézier formula imposes."},{"time":86724,"text":"On the right, ancient Gothic,"},{"time":89221,"text":"cut in the resistant material of steel by hand."},{"time":93280,"text":"None of the straight lines are actually straight."},{"time":95405,"text":"The curves are kind of subtle."},{"time":97570,"text":"It has that spark of life from the human hand"},{"time":102284,"text":"that the machine or the program"},{"time":104198,"text":"can never capture."},{"time":106131,"text":"What a contrast."}]},{"cues":[{"time":108110,"text":"Well, I tell a lie."},{"time":110689,"text":"A lie at TED. I'm really sorry."},{"time":113677,"text":"Both of these were made on a computer,"},{"time":115798,"text":"same software, same Bézier curves,"},{"time":117724,"text":"same font format."},{"time":119416,"text":"The one on your left"},{"time":121950,"text":"was made by Zuzana Licko at Emigre,"},{"time":124204,"text":"and I did the other one."},{"time":125639,"text":"The tool is the same, yet the letters are different."},{"time":128995,"text":"The letters are different"},{"time":130518,"text":"because the designers are different."},{"time":131724,"text":"That's all. Zuzana wanted hers to look like that."},{"time":134985,"text":"I wanted mine to look like that. End of story."},{"time":138106,"text":"Type is very adaptable."},{"time":140310,"text":"Unlike a fine art, such as sculpture or architecture,"},{"time":143631,"text":"type hides its methods."},{"time":147030,"text":"I think of myself as an industrial designer."},{"time":149827,"text":"The thing I design is manufactured,"},{"time":151393,"text":"and it has a function:"},{"time":153269,"text":"to be read, to convey meaning."},{"time":155107,"text":"But there is a bit more to it than that."},{"time":156753,"text":"There's the sort of aesthetic element."},{"time":158601,"text":"What makes these two letters different"},{"time":161317,"text":"from different interpretations by different designers?"},{"time":164349,"text":"What gives the work of some designers"},{"time":166362,"text":"sort of characteristic personal style,"},{"time":169273,"text":"as you might find in the work of a fashion designer,"},{"time":171810,"text":"an automobile designer, whatever?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":174885,"text":"There have been some cases, I admit,"},{"time":176660,"text":"where I as a designer"},{"time":177810,"text":"did feel the influence of technology."},{"time":180899,"text":"This is from the mid-'60s,"},{"time":183959,"text":"the change from metal type to photo,"},{"time":186194,"text":"hot to cold."},{"time":187896,"text":"This brought some benefits"},{"time":189093,"text":"but also one particular drawback:"},{"time":192439,"text":"a spacing system that only provided"},{"time":195112,"text":"18 discrete units for letters"},{"time":199095,"text":"to be accommodated on."},{"time":201558,"text":"I was asked at this time to design"},{"time":203534,"text":"a series of condensed sans serif types"},{"time":206272,"text":"with as many different variants as possible"},{"time":209435,"text":"within this 18-unit box."},{"time":213282,"text":"Quickly looking at the arithmetic,"},{"time":214921,"text":"I realized I could only actually make three"},{"time":218230,"text":"of related design. Here you see them."},{"time":221617,"text":"In Helvetica Compressed, Extra Compressed,"},{"time":224208,"text":"and Ultra Compressed, this rigid 18-unit system"},{"time":228019,"text":"really boxed me in."},{"time":229592,"text":"It kind of determined the proportions"},{"time":231425,"text":"of the design."},{"time":233714,"text":"Here are the typefaces, at least the lower cases."},{"time":237744,"text":"So do you look at these and say,"},{"time":240436,"text":"\"Poor Matthew, he had to submit to a problem,"},{"time":243575,"text":"and by God it shows in the results.\""},{"time":247382,"text":"I hope not."},{"time":248689,"text":"If I were doing this same job today,"},{"time":250930,"text":"instead of having 18 spacing units,"},{"time":253756,"text":"I would have 1,000."},{"time":256840,"text":"Clearly I could make more variants,"},{"time":259293,"text":"but would these three members\nof the family be better?"},{"time":263989,"text":"It's hard to say without actually doing it,"},{"time":265841,"text":"but they would not be better in the proportion"},{"time":267548,"text":"of 1,000 to 18, I can tell you that."},{"time":270637,"text":"My instinct tells you that any improvement"},{"time":272575,"text":"would be rather slight, because they were designed"},{"time":275653,"text":"as functions of the system they were designed to fit,"},{"time":278574,"text":"and as I said, type is very adaptable."},{"time":280983,"text":"It does hide its methods."},{"time":283770,"text":"All industrial designers work within constraints."},{"time":286452,"text":"This is not fine art."}]},{"cues":[{"time":288944,"text":"The question is, does a constraint"},{"time":290822,"text":"force a compromise?"},{"time":293489,"text":"By accepting a constraint,"},{"time":295000,"text":"are you working to a lower standard?"},{"time":297449,"text":"I don't believe so, and I've always been encouraged"},{"time":299411,"text":"by something that Charles Eames said."},{"time":301535,"text":"He said he was conscious of working"},{"time":303080,"text":"within constraints,"},{"time":304118,"text":"but not of making compromises."},{"time":307344,"text":"The distinction between a constraint"},{"time":309905,"text":"and a compromise is obviously very subtle,"},{"time":312280,"text":"but it's very central to my attitude to work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":317951,"text":"Remember this reading experience?"},{"time":320842,"text":"The phone book. I'll hold the slide"},{"time":322267,"text":"so you can enjoy the nostalgia."},{"time":326802,"text":"This is from the mid-'70s early trials"},{"time":329548,"text":"of Bell Centennial typeface I designed"},{"time":332177,"text":"for the U.S. phone books,"},{"time":333951,"text":"and it was my first experience of digital type,"},{"time":337270,"text":"and quite a baptism."},{"time":341440,"text":"Designed for the phone books, as I said,"},{"time":343039,"text":"to be printed at tiny size on newsprint"},{"time":346407,"text":"on very high-speed rotary presses"},{"time":348725,"text":"with ink that was kerosene and lampblack."},{"time":351477,"text":"This is not a hospitable environment"},{"time":355318,"text":"for a typographic designer."},{"time":358520,"text":"So the challenge for me was to design type"},{"time":360419,"text":"that performed as well as possible"},{"time":361920,"text":"in these very adverse production conditions."},{"time":366665,"text":"As I say, we were in the infancy of digital type."},{"time":369520,"text":"I had to draw every character by hand"},{"time":372339,"text":"on quadrille graph paper --"},{"time":374054,"text":"there were four weights of Bell Centennial —"},{"time":376006,"text":"pixel by pixel, then encode\nthem raster line by raster line"},{"time":379359,"text":"for the keyboard."},{"time":380340,"text":"It took two years, but I learned a lot."},{"time":384764,"text":"These letters look as though they've been chewed"},{"time":386394,"text":"by the dog or something or other,"},{"time":387838,"text":"but the missing pixels at the intersections"},{"time":389780,"text":"of strokes or in the crotches"},{"time":391385,"text":"are the result of my studying the effects"},{"time":394559,"text":"of ink spread on cheap paper"},{"time":397505,"text":"and reacting, revising the font accordingly."},{"time":401242,"text":"These strange artifacts are designed to compensate"},{"time":404492,"text":"for the undesirable effects of scale"},{"time":407244,"text":"and production process."},{"time":409530,"text":"At the outset, AT&amp;T had wanted"},{"time":412376,"text":"to set the phone books in Helvetica,"},{"time":415617,"text":"but as my friend Erik Spiekermann said"},{"time":417282,"text":"in the Helvetica movie, if you've seen that,"},{"time":419785,"text":"the letters in Helvetica were designed to be"},{"time":421820,"text":"as similar to one another as possible."},{"time":424561,"text":"This is not the recipe for legibility at small size."},{"time":427835,"text":"It looks very elegant up on a slide."},{"time":430425,"text":"I had to disambiguate these forms"},{"time":432615,"text":"of the figures as much as possible in Bell Centennial"},{"time":435615,"text":"by sort of opening the shapes up, as you can see"},{"time":437910,"text":"in the bottom part of that slide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":440823,"text":"So now we're on to the mid-'80s,"},{"time":443480,"text":"the early days of digital outline fonts,"},{"time":446036,"text":"vector technology."},{"time":448393,"text":"There was an issue at that time"},{"time":450431,"text":"with the size of the fonts,"},{"time":452287,"text":"the amount of data that was required to find"},{"time":455171,"text":"and store a font in computer memory."},{"time":460141,"text":"It limited the number of fonts you could get"},{"time":461799,"text":"on your typesetting system at any one time."},{"time":464789,"text":"I did an analysis of the data,"},{"time":468938,"text":"and found that a typical serif face"},{"time":471462,"text":"you see on the left"},{"time":472921,"text":"needed nearly twice as much data"},{"time":474937,"text":"as a sans serif in the middle"},{"time":477473,"text":"because of all the points required"},{"time":479535,"text":"to define the elegantly curved serif brackets."},{"time":484043,"text":"The numbers at the bottom of the slide, by the way,"},{"time":487477,"text":"they represent the amount of data"},{"time":489179,"text":"needed to store each of the fonts."},{"time":492984,"text":"So the sans serif, in the middle,"},{"time":495150,"text":"sans the serifs, was much more economical,"},{"time":498114,"text":"81 to 151."}]},{"cues":[{"time":500313,"text":"\"Aha,\" I thought. \"The engineers have a problem."},{"time":503970,"text":"Designer to the rescue.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":506205,"text":"I made a serif type, you can see it on the right,"},{"time":508552,"text":"without curved serifs."},{"time":510499,"text":"I made them polygonal, out\nof straight line segments,"},{"time":512915,"text":"chamfered brackets."},{"time":514898,"text":"And look, as economical in data as a sans serif."},{"time":519266,"text":"We call it Charter, on the right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":521565,"text":"So I went to the head of engineering"},{"time":523535,"text":"with my numbers, and I said proudly,"},{"time":525993,"text":"\"I have solved your problem.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":528121,"text":"\"Oh,\" he said. \"What problem?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":531834,"text":"And I said, \"Well, you know, the problem"},{"time":533480,"text":"of the huge data you require\nfor serif fonts and so on.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":536897,"text":"\"Oh,\" he said. \"We solved that problem last week."},{"time":540444,"text":"We wrote a compaction routine that reduces"},{"time":542600,"text":"the size of all fonts by an order of magnitude."},{"time":545180,"text":"You can have as many fonts on your system"},{"time":547168,"text":"as you like.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":548726,"text":"\"Well, thank you for letting me know,\" I said."}]},{"cues":[{"time":551340,"text":"Foiled again."},{"time":552970,"text":"I was left with a design solution"},{"time":555015,"text":"for a nonexistent technical problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":559488,"text":"But here is where the story sort\nof gets interesting for me."},{"time":561957,"text":"I didn't just throw my design away"},{"time":564552,"text":"in a fit of pique."},{"time":565953,"text":"I persevered."},{"time":567690,"text":"What had started as a technical exercise"},{"time":569858,"text":"became an aesthetic exercise, really."},{"time":573122,"text":"In other words, I had come to like this typeface."},{"time":576171,"text":"Forget its origins. Screw that."},{"time":578490,"text":"I liked the design for its own sake."},{"time":580980,"text":"The simplified forms of Charter"},{"time":583363,"text":"gave it a sort of plain-spoken quality"},{"time":585446,"text":"and unfussy spareness"},{"time":586997,"text":"that sort of pleased me."},{"time":589487,"text":"You know, at times of technical innovation,"},{"time":592040,"text":"designers want to be influenced"},{"time":593560,"text":"by what's in the air."},{"time":595296,"text":"We want to respond. We want to be pushed"},{"time":597527,"text":"into exploring something new."},{"time":600938,"text":"So Charter is a sort of parable for me, really."},{"time":603837,"text":"In the end, there was no hard and fast causal link"},{"time":607627,"text":"between the technology and the design of Charter."},{"time":610820,"text":"I had really misunderstood the technology."},{"time":614582,"text":"The technology did suggest something to me,"},{"time":617910,"text":"but it did not force my hand,"},{"time":620027,"text":"and I think this happens very often."}]},{"cues":[{"time":622744,"text":"You know, engineers are very smart,"},{"time":625370,"text":"and despite occasional frustrations"},{"time":626926,"text":"because I'm less smart,"},{"time":628453,"text":"I've always enjoyed working with them"},{"time":630180,"text":"and learning from them."},{"time":632258,"text":"Apropos, in the mid-'90s,"},{"time":634600,"text":"I started talking to Microsoft"},{"time":637291,"text":"about screen fonts."},{"time":639679,"text":"Up to that point, all the fonts on screen"},{"time":642100,"text":"had been adapted from previously existing"},{"time":644853,"text":"printing fonts, of course."},{"time":647230,"text":"But Microsoft foresaw correctly"},{"time":649733,"text":"the movement, the stampede"},{"time":651883,"text":"towards electronic communication,"},{"time":654670,"text":"to reading and writing onscreen"},{"time":656700,"text":"with the printed output as being sort of secondary"},{"time":659833,"text":"in importance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":662056,"text":"So the priorities were just tipping at that point."},{"time":665635,"text":"They wanted a small core set of fonts"},{"time":667829,"text":"that were not adapted but designed for the screen"},{"time":671134,"text":"to face up to the problems of screen,"},{"time":673707,"text":"which were their coarse resolution displays."},{"time":677549,"text":"I said to Microsoft, a typeface designed"},{"time":681080,"text":"for a particular technology"},{"time":682649,"text":"is a self-obsoleting typeface."},{"time":686024,"text":"I've designed too many faces in the past"},{"time":688118,"text":"that were intended to mitigate technical problems."},{"time":691697,"text":"Thanks to the engineers, the\ntechnical problems went away."},{"time":694532,"text":"So did my typeface."},{"time":697021,"text":"It was only a stopgap."},{"time":700152,"text":"Microsoft came back to say that"},{"time":701693,"text":"affordable computer monitors"},{"time":703323,"text":"with better resolutions"},{"time":704520,"text":"were at least a decade away."},{"time":707116,"text":"So I thought, well, a decade, that's not bad,"},{"time":709770,"text":"that's more than a stopgap."}]},{"cues":[{"time":712182,"text":"So I was persuaded, I was convinced,"},{"time":714183,"text":"and we went to work on what became Verdana"},{"time":716505,"text":"and Georgia,"},{"time":718177,"text":"for the first time working not on paper"},{"time":720517,"text":"but directly onto the screen from the pixel up."},{"time":724477,"text":"At that time, screens were binary."},{"time":728330,"text":"The pixel was either on or it was off."},{"time":731370,"text":"Here you see the outline of a letter,"},{"time":734225,"text":"the cap H,"},{"time":735692,"text":"which is the thin black line, the contour,"},{"time":738493,"text":"which is how it is stored in memory,"},{"time":741369,"text":"superimposed on the bitmap,"},{"time":743039,"text":"which is the grey area,"},{"time":745187,"text":"which is how it's displayed on the screen."},{"time":747024,"text":"The bitmap is rasterized from the outline."},{"time":750170,"text":"Here in a cap H, which is all straight lines,"},{"time":752411,"text":"the two are in almost perfect sync"},{"time":754499,"text":"on the Cartesian grid."},{"time":758867,"text":"Not so with an O."},{"time":761993,"text":"This looks more like bricklaying\nthan type design,"},{"time":764720,"text":"but believe me, this is a good bitmap O,"},{"time":767621,"text":"for the simple reason that it's symmetrical"},{"time":769636,"text":"in both x and y axes."},{"time":772116,"text":"In a binary bitmap, you actually can't ask"},{"time":774974,"text":"for more than that."},{"time":776694,"text":"I would sometimes make, I don't know,"},{"time":779098,"text":"three or four different versions of a difficult letter"},{"time":781454,"text":"like a lowercase A,"},{"time":782960,"text":"and then stand back to choose which was the best."},{"time":786500,"text":"Well, there was no best,"},{"time":788595,"text":"so the designer's judgment comes in"},{"time":791020,"text":"in trying to decide"},{"time":792409,"text":"which is the least bad."},{"time":795450,"text":"Is that a compromise?"},{"time":797900,"text":"Not to me, if you are working"},{"time":799446,"text":"at the highest standard the technology will allow,"},{"time":802533,"text":"although that standard may be"},{"time":804742,"text":"well short of the ideal."},{"time":807221,"text":"You may be able to see on this slide"},{"time":808812,"text":"two different bitmap fonts there."},{"time":810974,"text":"The \"a\" in the upper one, I think,"},{"time":812670,"text":"is better than the \"a\" in the lower one,"},{"time":814583,"text":"but it still ain't great."},{"time":817159,"text":"You can maybe see the effect better"},{"time":819066,"text":"if it's reduced. Well, maybe not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":822442,"text":"So I'm a pragmatist, not an idealist,"},{"time":824838,"text":"out of necessity."},{"time":826341,"text":"For a certain kind of temperament,"},{"time":828270,"text":"there is a certain kind of satisfaction"},{"time":829970,"text":"in doing something that cannot be perfect"},{"time":833608,"text":"but can still be done to the best of your ability."},{"time":837477,"text":"Here's the lowercase H from Georgia Italic."},{"time":842334,"text":"The bitmap looks jagged and rough."},{"time":844607,"text":"It is jagged and rough."},{"time":846466,"text":"But I discovered, by experiment,"},{"time":848462,"text":"that there is an optimum slant"},{"time":851679,"text":"for an italic on a screen"},{"time":853625,"text":"so the strokes break well"},{"time":855957,"text":"at the pixel boundaries."},{"time":858440,"text":"Look in this example how, rough as it is,"},{"time":861221,"text":"how the left and right legs"},{"time":863271,"text":"actually break at the same level."},{"time":865220,"text":"That's a victory. That's good, right there."},{"time":868740,"text":"And of course, at the lower depths,"},{"time":871918,"text":"you don't get much choice."},{"time":873841,"text":"This is an S, in case you were wondering."}]},{"cues":[{"time":878886,"text":"Well, it's been 18 years now"},{"time":881040,"text":"since Verdana and Georgia were released."},{"time":883690,"text":"Microsoft were absolutely right,"},{"time":885780,"text":"it took a good 10 years,"},{"time":888194,"text":"but screen displays now do have"},{"time":890474,"text":"improved spatial resolution,"},{"time":892927,"text":"and very much improved photometric resolution"},{"time":896399,"text":"thanks to anti-aliasing and so on."},{"time":899553,"text":"So now that their mission is accomplished,"},{"time":903250,"text":"has that meant the demise"},{"time":904980,"text":"of the screen fonts that I designed"},{"time":906860,"text":"for coarser displays back then?"},{"time":909511,"text":"Will they outlive the now-obsolete screens"},{"time":912906,"text":"and the flood of new web fonts"},{"time":915078,"text":"coming on to the market?"},{"time":916581,"text":"Or have they established their own"},{"time":918441,"text":"sort of evolutionary niche"},{"time":920679,"text":"that is independent of technology?"},{"time":924416,"text":"In other words, have they been absorbed"},{"time":926087,"text":"into the typographic mainstream?"},{"time":929400,"text":"I'm not sure, but they've had a good run so far."},{"time":933058,"text":"Hey, 18 is a good age for anything"},{"time":935553,"text":"with present-day rates of attrition,"},{"time":937704,"text":"so I'm not complaining."}]},{"cues":[{"time":939618,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":942457,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}